{
  "text": "Proxy respondents were questioned when the patient was unable to provide all the requested information. On the basis of clinical [CITATION_1] and neuroradiological criteria, it was possible to distinguish patients as having lacunar or nonlacunar syndromes (including total anterior, partial anterior, and posterior syndromes). The severity of the neurological deficit was measured by means of the Canadian Neurological Scale (CNS), [CITATION_2] administered on admission and after 3, 5, and 7 days.",
